#Approach:

Approach:
Ye code string ko reverse karne ke liye stack ka LIFO principle use karta hai.

1. Pehle string ke sab characters ko stack me push kar dete hain.
2. Stack LIFO (Last In First Out) follow karta hai,
   isliye jo last character push hua tha wo sabse pehle pop hoga.
3. Ab stack se ek-ek character pop karke new char array me daalte jaate hain.
4. Isse string reverse order me mil jaati hai.

Main idea:
Stack ka LIFO nature string reverse karne me help karta hai:
Push → a b c d
Pop → d c b a

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(n)

#Code:

import java.util.Deque;
import java.util.ArrayDeque; 

public class Solution {
    public char[] reverseString(char[] s) {
        //You can code here

        Deque<Character> stack = new ArrayDeque<>();
        int n = s.length;

        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
          stack.push(s[i]);
        }

        char[] newString = new char[n];

        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
          newString[i] = stack.pop();
        }

        return newString;
      
    }
}
